defs.docs:
encoding_rs is a Gecko-oriented Free Software / Open Source implementation
 of the [Encoding Standard](https://encoding.spec.whatwg.org/) in Rust.
 Gecko-oriented means that converting to and from UTF-16 is supported in
 addition to converting to and from UTF-8, that the performance and
 streamability goals are browser-oriented, and that FFI-friendliness is a
 goal.

defs.name: mem
defs.docs:
Functions for converting between different in-RAM representations of text
 and for quickly checking if the Unicode Bidirectional Algorithm can be
 avoided.

defs.name: LeftToRight
defs.docs:
There is at least one character that's U+0100 or higher, but there
 are no right-to-left characters.

defs.name: Bidi
defs.docs: There is at least one right-to-left character.

defs.name: Latin1Bidi
defs.docs:
Classification of text as Latin1 (all code points are below U+0100),
 left-to-right with some non-Latin1 characters or as containing at least
 some right-to-left characters.

defs.name: is_ascii
defs.docs: Checks whether the buffer is all-ASCII.

defs.name: is_basic_latin
defs.docs:
Checks whether the buffer is all-Basic Latin (i.e. UTF-16 representing
 only ASCII characters).

defs.name: is_utf8_latin1
defs.docs:
Checks whether the buffer is valid UTF-8 representing only code points
 less than or equal to U+00FF.

defs.name: is_str_latin1
defs.docs:
Checks whether the buffer represents only code points less than or equal
 to U+00FF.

defs.name: is_utf16_latin1
defs.docs:
Checks whether the buffer represents only code point less than or equal
 to U+00FF.

defs.name: is_utf8_bidi
defs.docs:
Checks whether a potentially-invalid UTF-8 buffer contains code points
 that trigger right-to-left processing.

defs.name: is_str_bidi
defs.docs:
Checks whether a valid UTF-8 buffer contains code points that trigger
 right-to-left processing.

defs.name: is_utf16_bidi
defs.docs:
Checks whether a UTF-16 buffer contains code points that trigger
 right-to-left processing.

defs.name: is_char_bidi
defs.docs: Checks whether a scalar value triggers right-to-left processing.

defs.name: is_utf16_code_unit_bidi
defs.docs: Checks whether a UTF-16 code unit triggers right-to-left processing.

defs.name: check_utf8_for_latin1_and_bidi
defs.docs:
Checks whether a potentially invalid UTF-8 buffer contains code points
 that trigger right-to-left processing or is all-Latin1.

defs.name: check_str_for_latin1_and_bidi
defs.docs:
Checks whether a valid UTF-8 buffer contains code points
 that trigger right-to-left processing or is all-Latin1.

defs.name: check_utf16_for_latin1_and_bidi
defs.docs:
Checks whether a potentially invalid UTF-16 buffer contains code points
 that trigger right-to-left processing or is all-Latin1.

defs.name: convert_utf8_to_utf16
defs.docs:
Converts potentially-invalid UTF-8 to valid UTF-16 with errors replaced
 with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER.

defs.name: convert_str_to_utf16
defs.docs: Converts valid UTF-8 to valid UTF-16.

defs.name: convert_utf8_to_utf16_without_replacement
defs.docs: Converts potentially-invalid UTF-8 to valid UTF-16 signaling on error.

defs.name: convert_utf16_to_utf8_partial
defs.docs:
Converts potentially-invalid UTF-16 to valid UTF-8 with errors replaced
 with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER with potentially insufficient output
 space.

defs.name: convert_utf16_to_utf8
defs.docs:
Converts potentially-invalid UTF-16 to valid UTF-8 with errors replaced
 with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER.

defs.name: convert_utf16_to_str_partial
defs.docs:
Converts potentially-invalid UTF-16 to valid UTF-8 with errors replaced
 with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER such that the validity of the output is
 signaled using the Rust type system with potentially insufficient output
 space.

defs.name: convert_utf16_to_str
defs.docs:
Converts potentially-invalid UTF-16 to valid UTF-8 with errors replaced
 with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER such that the validity of the output is
 signaled using the Rust type system.

defs.name: convert_latin1_to_utf16
defs.docs:
Converts bytes whose unsigned value is interpreted as Unicode code point
 (i.e. U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive) to UTF-16.

defs.name: convert_latin1_to_utf8_partial
defs.docs:
Converts bytes whose unsigned value is interpreted as Unicode code point
 (i.e. U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive) to UTF-8 with potentially insufficient
 output space.

defs.name: convert_latin1_to_utf8
defs.docs:
Converts bytes whose unsigned value is interpreted as Unicode code point
 (i.e. U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive) to UTF-8.

defs.name: convert_latin1_to_str_partial
defs.docs:
Converts bytes whose unsigned value is interpreted as Unicode code point
 (i.e. U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive) to UTF-8 such that the validity of the
 output is signaled using the Rust type system with potentially insufficient
 output space.

defs.name: convert_latin1_to_str
defs.docs:
Converts bytes whose unsigned value is interpreted as Unicode code point
 (i.e. U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive) to UTF-8 such that the validity of the
 output is signaled using the Rust type system.

defs.name: convert_utf8_to_latin1_lossy
defs.docs:
If the input is valid UTF-8 representing only Unicode code points from
 U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive, converts the input into output that
 represents the value of each code point as the unsigned byte value of
 each output byte.

defs.name: convert_utf16_to_latin1_lossy
defs.docs:
If the input is valid UTF-16 representing only Unicode code points from
 U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive, converts the input into output that
 represents the value of each code point as the unsigned byte value of
 each output byte.

defs.name: decode_latin1
defs.docs:
Converts bytes whose unsigned value is interpreted as Unicode code point
 (i.e. U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive) to UTF-8.

defs.name: encode_latin1_lossy
defs.docs:
If the input is valid UTF-8 representing only Unicode code points from
 U+0000 to U+00FF, inclusive, converts the input into output that
 represents the value of each code point as the unsigned byte value of
 each output byte.

defs.name: utf16_valid_up_to
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the first unpaired surrogate or, if the input is
 valid UTF-16 in its entirety, the length of the input.

defs.name: utf8_latin1_up_to
defs.docs:
Returns the index of first byte that starts an invalid byte
 sequence or a non-Latin1 byte sequence, or the length of the
 string if there are neither.

defs.name: str_latin1_up_to
defs.docs:
Returns the index of first byte that starts a non-Latin1 byte
 sequence, or the length of the string if there are none.

defs.name: ensure_utf16_validity
defs.docs: Replaces unpaired surrogates in the input with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER.

defs.name: copy_ascii_to_ascii
defs.docs:
Copies ASCII from source to destination up to the first non-ASCII byte
 (or the end of the input if it is ASCII in its entirety).

defs.name: copy_ascii_to_basic_latin
defs.docs:
Copies ASCII from source to destination zero-extending it to UTF-16 up to
 the first non-ASCII byte (or the end of the input if it is ASCII in its
 entirety).

defs.name: copy_basic_latin_to_ascii
defs.docs:
Copies Basic Latin from source to destination narrowing it to ASCII up to
 the first non-Basic Latin code unit (or the end of the input if it is
 Basic Latin in its entirety).

defs.name: Encoding
defs.docs: An encoding as defined in the [Encoding Standard][1].

defs.name: for_label_no_replacement
defs.docs:
This method behaves the same as `for_label()`, except when `for_label()`
 would return `Some(REPLACEMENT)`, this method returns `None` instead.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns the name of this encoding.

defs.name: can_encode_everything
defs.docs:
Checks whether the _output encoding_ of this encoding can encode every
 `char`. (Only true if the output encoding is UTF-8.)

defs.name: is_ascii_compatible
defs.docs:
Checks whether the bytes 0x00...0x7F map exclusively to the characters
 U+0000...U+007F and vice versa.

defs.name: is_single_byte
defs.docs:
Checks whether this encoding maps one byte to one Basic Multilingual
 Plane code point (i.e. byte length equals decoded UTF-16 length) and
 vice versa (for mappable characters).

defs.name: output_encoding
defs.docs:
Returns the _output encoding_ of this encoding. This is UTF-8 for
 UTF-16BE, UTF-16LE and replacement and the encoding itself otherwise.

defs.name: decode
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'static self, bytes: &'a [u8]) -> (Cow<'a, str>, &'static Encoding, bool)
defs.docs:
Decode complete input to `Cow<'a, str>` _with BOM sniffing_ and with
 malformed sequences replaced with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER when the
 entire input is available as a single buffer (i.e. the end of the
 buffer marks the end of the stream).

defs.name: decode_with_bom_removal
defs.docs:
Decode complete input to `Cow<'a, str>` _with BOM removal_ and with
 malformed sequences replaced with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER when the
 entire input is available as a single buffer (i.e. the end of the
 buffer marks the end of the stream).

defs.name: decode_without_bom_handling
defs.docs:
Decode complete input to `Cow<'a, str>` _without BOM handling_ and
 with malformed sequences replaced with the REPLACEMENT CHARACTER when
 the entire input is available as a single buffer (i.e. the end of the
 buffer marks the end of the stream).

defs.name: decode_without_bom_handling_and_without_replacement
defs.docs:
Decode complete input to `Cow<'a, str>` _without BOM handling_ and
 _with malformed sequences treated as fatal_ when the entire input is
 available as a single buffer (i.e. the end of the buffer marks the end
 of the stream).

defs.name: encode
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'static self, string: &'a str) -> (Cow<'a, [u8]>, &'static Encoding, bool)
defs.docs:
Encode complete input to `Cow<'a, [u8]>` with unmappable characters
 replaced with decimal numeric character references when the entire input
 is available as a single buffer (i.e. the end of the buffer marks the
 end of the stream).

defs.name: new_decoder
defs.docs: Instantiates a new decoder for this encoding with BOM sniffing enabled.

defs.name: new_decoder_with_bom_removal
defs.docs: Instantiates a new decoder for this encoding with BOM removal.

defs.name: new_decoder_without_bom_handling
defs.docs: Instantiates a new decoder for this encoding with BOM handling disabled.

defs.name: new_encoder
defs.docs: Instantiates a new encoder for the output encoding of this encoding.

defs.name: OutputFull
defs.docs:
The converter cannot produce another unit of output, because the output
 buffer does not have enough space left.

defs.name: CoderResult
defs.docs:
Result of a (potentially partial) decode or encode operation with
 replacement.

defs.name: OutputFull
defs.docs:
The decoder cannot produce another unit of output, because the output
 buffer does not have enough space left.

defs.name: Malformed
defs.docs: The decoder encountered a malformed byte sequence.

defs.name: DecoderResult
defs.docs: Result of a (potentially partial) decode operation without replacement.

defs.name: Decoder
defs.docs:
A converter that decodes a byte stream into Unicode according to a
 character encoding in a streaming (incremental) manner.

defs.docs: Query the worst-case UTF-8 output size _with replacement_.

defs.name: max_utf8_buffer_length_without_replacement

defs.value: fn (&mut self, src: &[u8], dst: &mut [u8], last: bool) -> (CoderResult, usize, usize, bool)
defs.docs:

defs.value: fn (&mut self, src: &[u8], dst: &mut String, last: bool) -> (DecoderResult, usize)
defs.docs: Incrementally decode a byte stream into UTF-8 using a `String` receiver.

A converter that encodes a Unicode stream into bytes according to a

Returns `true` if this is an ISO-2022-JP encoder that's not in the
 ASCII state and `false` otherwise.
